This article is a transcript of a press gaggle with White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest, in July 2015. Earnest discusses President Obama's upcoming events, including a speech at the VFW National Convention, an interview with Jon Stewart, and an event for the Democratic Senatorial Campaign Committee. He also mentions the White House's new online tools to advocate for the Iran nuclear deal. Earnest responds to questions about the President's remarks at the convention, criticism of the VA, security concerns at military installations, predatory lending targeting military families, comments made by Iran's Supreme Leader, concerns about an arms race in the Middle East, an investigation into excessive spending by the Israeli Prime Minister, the highway bill, the use of personal email by DHS employees, and a call between President Obama and President Xi of China.